50|$|The Kalmyk people — or Kalmyks — is {{the name}} given to the Oirats, western Mongols in Russia, whose {{ancestors}} migrated from Dzhungaria in 1607. Today they form {{a majority in the}} autonomous Republic of <b>Kalmykia</b> on the western shore of the Caspian Sea. <b>Kalmykia</b> has Europe's only Buddhist government.|$|E
